            <p><strong>Disk Space<a name=\'vh1\'></a><br>
            </strong>Disk space is measured in megabytes (MB). The Basic plan has 200 megabytes of disk space allocated to it. That means you can store more than 13,000 static web pages or 20,000+ dynamic pages. The Power plan has more than double that capacity, and the e-commerce package has more than four times that capacity. </p>
            <p align=\'right\'> <img src=\'images/ar4.gif\' alt=\'\' width=\'7\' height=\'7\'> <a href=\'#top\'>Back to top</a></p>            <p><strong>Data Transfer<a name=\'vh2\'></a><br>
            </strong>Data transfer is measured in megabytes (MB). Data transfer is any data that comes in to your site or is sent out from it. The Basic plan offers 10,000 MB of data transfer per month. This is roughly 500,000 page-views per month or 35,000 unique visitors per month - more than enough capacity for most web sites. The Power plan doubles that capacity, and the E-commerce plan is more than 3 times that capacity. </p>
            <p align=\'right\'> <img src=\'images/ar4.gif\' alt=\'\' width=\'7\' height=\'7\'> <a href=\'#top\'>Back to top</a></p>            <p><strong>POP Email Accounts<a name=\'vh3\'></a><br>
              </strong>POP Email accounts are the number of real email accounts that you are allocated. These can be created and removed in the cPanel account control panel. Each POP email box has its own username and password login, and it\'s own webmail interface. The format for email addresses is <strong>username@yourdomain.com </strong></p>
            <p align=\'right\'> <img src=\'images/ar4.gif\' alt=\'\' width=\'7\' height=\'7\'> <a href=\'#top\'>Back to top</a></p>            <p><strong>Number of Domains<a name=\'vh4\'></a><br>
            </strong>This is the number of top level domain names that can be hosted on the plan in question. The Basic plan allows one top level domain. The Power package allows 3 top level domains, which means 3 unique and completely separate web sites if you choose to have them. The E-commerce plan allows unlimited domains since it is a reseller account, and you may have many customers with their own domain names. </p>
            <p align=\'right\'> <img src=\'images/ar4.gif\' alt=\'\' width=\'7\' height=\'7\'> <a href=\'#top\'>Back to top</a></p>            <p><strong>IP Address<a name=\'vh5\'></a><br>
